ly records and game results from 1962\u20132012, ''see'' Media Guide 2013\u201314, pp.130\u201341.</ref>\n\n{{CBB Yearly Record Start\n|type=team\n|conference=\n|postseason=\n|poll=no\n}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record Subhead|\n|name=[[Bob King (basketball)|Bob King]]\n|startyear=1962\n|conference=[[Western Athletic Conference]]\n|endyear=1972\n|}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record Entry\n | championship =\n | season       = 1962\u20131963\n | name         = Bob King\n | overall      = 16\u20139\n | conference   = 4\u20136\n | confstanding = 4th\n | postseason   = \n}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record Entry\n | championship = conference\n | season       = 1963\u20131964\n | name         = Bob King\n | overall      = 23\u20136\n |conference    = 7\u20133\n |confstanding  = T-1st\n | postseason   = [[1964 National Invitation Tournament|NIT]] Runner-up\n}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record Entry\n | championship =\n | season       = 1964\u20131965\n | name         = Bob King\n | overall      = 19\u20138\n |conference    = 5\u20135\n |confstanding  = T-2nd\n | postseason   = [[1965 National Invitation Tournament|NIT]] 2nd Round\n}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record Entry\n | championship =\n | season       = 1965\u20131966\n | name         = Bob King\n | overall      = 16\u20138\n |conference    = 4\u20136\n |confstanding  = 5th\n | postseason   =\n}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record Entry\n | championship =\n | season       = 1966\u20131967\n | name         = Bob King\n | overall      = 19\u20138\n |conference    = 5\u20135\n |confstanding  = T-3rd\n | postseason   = [[1967 National Invitation Tournament|NIT]] 2nd Round\n}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record Entry\n | championship = conference\n | season       = 1967\u20131968\n | name         = Bob King\n | overall      = 23\u20135\n |conference    = 8\u20132\n |confstanding  = 1st\n | postseason = [[1968 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|NCAA]] Regional Fourth Place\n}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record Entry\n | championship =\n | season       = 1968\u20131969\n | name         = Bob King\n | overall    