vada\n|[[Trey Kell]], San Diego State\n|}\n\n===NCAA tournament===\nNew Mexico has a history of disappointing performances in the [[NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|NCAA tournament]], suffering noteworthy upsets in 1968, 1978, 1993, 2010, 2013, and 2014. Nevertheless, they have won at least one game in six of their last nine appearances. The Lobos have made 15 appearances in the NCAA tournament, compiling an overall record of 8\u201316.<ref>Media Guide 2013-14, pp.113-20.</ref>\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align:center\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=New Mexico Lobos|Year|Seed|Round|Opponent|Result}}\n|-\n| [[1968 NCAA University Division Basketball Tournament|1968]] || style=\"background:#E6E8FA;\"| || Round of 23<br>Sweet Sixteen<br>Regional 3rd place<!-- game-->|| Bye<br>[[Santa Clara Broncos men's basketball|Santa Clara]]<br>[[New Mexico State Aggies men's basketball|New Mexico State]] || \u2014<br>L 73\u201386<br>L 58\u201362\n|-\n| [[1974 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|1974]] || style=\"background:#E6E8FA;\"| || Round of 25<br>Sweet Sixteen<br>Regional 3rd place<!-- game-->|| [[Idaho State Bengals men's basketball|Idaho State]]<br>[[San Francisco Dons men's basketball|San Francisco]]<br>[[Dayton Flyers men's basketball|Dayton]] || '''W''' 73\u201365<br>L 61\u201364<br>'''W''' 66\u201361\n|-\n| [[1978 NCAA Division I Basketball Tournament|1978]] || style=\"background:#E6E8FA;\"| || Round of 32 || [[Cal State Fullerton Titans men's basketball|Cal State Fullerton]] || L 85\u201390\n|-\n| [[1991 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|1991]] || 14 E || Round of 64 || (3) [[Oklahoma State Cowboys basketball|Oklahoma State]] || L 54\u201367\n|-\n| [[1993 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|1993]] || 5 W || Round of 64 || (12) [[George Washington Colonials men's basketball|George Washington]] || L 68\u201382\n|-\n| [[1994 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|1994]] || 10 W || Round of 64 || (7) [[Virginia Cavaliers men's 